structured.description: A PageInfo class that encapsulates information about pagination in a Spring Data JPA application. The PageInfo class is created using a static method "of" which takes a Pageable object and a Page object as parameters. This method calculates and sets the values for currentPage, pageLimit, totalPages, and totalElements fields based on the input objects.

items.description: Represents paginated data and provides information about the current page of a dataset. It is used to encapsulate pagination metadata such as the current page number, total pages, total elements, and page size. The class has a static factory method that creates a PageInfo object from a Pageable and a Page objects.
items.name: PageInfo

items.description: Creates an instance of the `PageInfo` class, initializing it with parameters from a `Pageable` object and a `Page` object. The resulting `PageInfo` contains page number, page size, total pages, and total elements from the given pagination data.

params.name: pageable
params.description: pagination information, providing methods to retrieve the current page number and size.

params.name: page
params.description: result of the pagination operation, providing information about the total number of pages and elements.

items.name: of

structured.description: A configuration class that enables Cross-Origin Resource Sharing (CORS) in a Spring-based web application. The configuration allows incoming requests from any origin and specifies allowed HTTP methods, headers, and credentials. It uses the Spring Web MVC framework and the CorsRegistry to configure CORS settings for the web application.

items.description: Is used to configure CORS (Cross-Origin Resource Sharing) settings for a web application. It allows requests from specified origins and specifies allowed HTTP methods, headers, and credentials. The class provides a bean that adds CORS mappings to the registry, allowing incoming requests from any origin and specifying allowed methods, headers, and credentials.
items.name: CorsConfig

items.description: Allows incoming requests from any origin and specifies allowed methods, headers, and credentials by adding CORS mappings to a registry. It sets all origins as allowed, all HTTP methods, all headers, exposes specific headers, and allows credentials for making requests to the server.

returns.description:
a configuration for CORS mappings.

* It is an instance of `WebMvcConfigurer`, which represents a configuration for a Web application.
* The output is used to configure CORS (Cross-Origin Resource Sharing) in the application.
* The main attributes are:
  - `allowedOrigins`: An array of allowed origins, specifying the domains or subdomains that can make CORS requests to the server.
  - `allowedMethods`: An array of allowed HTTP methods, specifying the methods that can be used in CORS requests.
  - `allowedHeaders`: An array of allowed headers, specifying the headers that can be included in CORS responses from the server.
  - `exposedHeaders`: An array of exposed headers, specifying the headers that can be included in CORS responses and are visible to clients.
  - `allowCredentials`: A boolean value indicating whether CORS requests with credentials (such as cookies or authentication tokens) are allowed.

items.name: corsConfigurer

items.description: Enables Cross-Origin Resource Sharing (CORS) for a Spring Boot application, allowing requests from specified origins to access resources. It defines global CORS settings for all URLs by mapping "/**" and specifying allowed origins, methods, headers, and exposed headers.

params.name: registry
params.description: configuration object that allows to add and manage CORS (Cross-Origin Resource Sharing) configurations for the Spring application.

items.name: addCorsMappings
